Step-by-Step Example
1. üîß Define Variables in variables.tf
hcl
Copy
Edit
variable "from_port" {
  type        = number
  description = "Start of the port range for ingress rule"
}

variable "to_port" {
  type        = number
  description = "End of the port range for ingress rule"
}

variable "ingress_cidrs" {
  type        = list(string)
  description = "CIDRs allowed to access the port range"
}

variable "egress_cidrs" {
  type        = list(string)
  description = "CIDRs allowed for egress"
}
2. üèóÔ∏è Use Variables in main.tf
h
Copy
Edit
resource "aws_security_group" "oracle_sg" {
  name        = "oracle-db-sg"
  description = "Allow access to Oracle DB port range"
  vpc_id      = var.vpc_id

  dynamic "ingress" {
    for_each = var.ingress_cidrs
    content {
      from_port   = var.from_port
      to_port     = var.to_port
      protocol    = "tcp"
      cidr_blocks = [ingress.value]
    }
  }

  dynamic "egress" {
    for_each = var.egress_cidrs
    content {
      from_port   = 0
      to_port     = 0
      protocol    = "-1"
      cidr_blocks = [egress.value]
    }
  }
}
3. üìÑ terraform.tfvars
hcl
Copy
Edit
from_port     = 1525
to_port       = 1525

ingress_cidrs = [
  "10.0.0.0/24",
  "192.168.0.0/24"
]

egress_cidrs = [
  "0.0.0.0/0"
]
‚úÖ Bonus: Allow a Range (e.g. 1521-1530)
If you want to allow a full range instead of just one port:

hcl
Copy
Edit
from_port = 1521
to_port   = 1530
This will allow TCP traffic on all ports between 1521 and 1530.

